      "message": "nit: Maybe worth documenting here: assuming the caller is calling this function periodically with a period P, \"since\" should be P + L, where L is the longest task duration among the tasks that we care about. That\u0027s because provider is searching by task start time, but will only return results for completed tasks. So, if a task finished P seconds ago and took L seconds to finish, the start time would be P+L seconds ago.\n\n(I meant to mention this after you clarified the documentation for TaskListProvider, but I forgot.)",
